						<div class="postbody">Yeah, you'd naively hope that the N64 480i mode would actually re-render the 3D scene every 60Hz and thus be able to ultimately render each refresh at â‰ˆ300x224.<br /><br />For good and ill, the N64 instead gives you a plain 448-pixel high framebuffer and the output stage (the creatively named Video Interface) draws from that framebuffer, optionally with flicker reduction (which is a vertical 1 2 1 filter)</div>

